1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,400
Ever wondered how neurons send messages?

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:04,800
It all starts with electrical spikes.

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:08,400
These spikes trigger the release of chemicals called neurotransmitters.

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:12,000
But how do these neurotransmitters know where to go?

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,200
They travel across tiny gaps known as synapses!

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:19,600
This chemical communication is essential for everything from movement to memory.

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,200
Curious about the brain?

8
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,600
Follow for more insights into neuroscience!
